<p>In my client code, I am trying to call to a tomcat server in the same box. And I am getting following error.But this happens intermittently. Not always. But in a bit frequent manner.</p>  <p>Here is what my client looks like.</p>  <pre><code>  public int send(Message message) throws GeneralSecurityException, IOException {     int result = 0;     Protocol.registerProtocol("https", new Protocol("https", new EasySSLProtocolSocketFactory(), port));     PostMethod post = new PostMethod(urlPath);     RequestEntity entity = new StringRequestEntity(message.getMessage(), contentType, "UTF-8");     post.setRequestEntity(entity);     post.setRequestHeader(Names.CONNECTION,Values.KEEP_ALIVE);     try {         result = httpclient.executeMethod(post);         if(result != 200) {             LOG.error("Invalid response came from dispatch endpoint. url=" + urlPath + ", response-code = " + result + ", message = " + post.getResponseBodyAsString());         }     } finally {         post.releaseConnection();         httpclient.getHttpConnectionManager().closeIdleConnections(0);     }     return result; } </code></pre>  <p>Here is the error log. And seems some idle, staled connections being reused and hence this issue ?</p>  <p>org.apache.commons.httpclient.NoHttpResponseException: The server 127.0.0.1 failed to respond     at org.apache.commons.httpclient.HttpMethodBase.readStatusLine(HttpMethodBase.java:1976)     at org.apache.commons.httpclient.HttpMethodBase.readResponse(HttpMethodBase.java:1735)     at org.apache.commons.httpclient.HttpMethodBase.execute(HttpMethodBase.java:1098)     at org.apache.commons.httpclient.HttpMethodDirector.executeWithRetry(HttpMethodDirector.java:398)     at org.apache.commons.httpclient.HttpMethodDirector.executeMethod(HttpMethodDirector.java:171)     at org.apache.commons.httpclient.HttpClient.executeMethod(HttpClient.java:397)     at org.apache.commons.httpclient.HttpClient.executeMethod(HttpClient.java:323)</p>